sswire.com/news/home/20051003006052/en/Jimmy-Wales-Joins-Socialtext-Board-Directors-Wikipedia|accessdate=December 26, 2017}}</ref><ref name=garlick>{{cite news|last=Garlick|first=Mia|title=Creative Commons Adds Two New Board Members|date=March 30, 2006|publisher=[[Creative Commons]]|accessdate=October 31, 2008|url=https://creativecommons.org/press-releases/entry/5840|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081222104046/http://creativecommons.org/press-releases/entry/5840|archivedate=December 22, 2008|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=knox>{{cite web|url=http://www.knox.edu/x12330.xml|title=Knox College Honorary Degrees|website=Knox College|accessdate=October 31, 2008|archivedate=September 2, 2006|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060902200844/http://www.knox.edu/x12330.xml|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n<ref name=infozine>{{cite news|url=http://www.infozine.com/news/stories/op/storiesView/sid/14632|title=EFF Honors Craigslist, Gigi Sohn, and Jimmy Wales with Pioneer Awards|date=April 28, 2006|work=Kansas City infoZine News|accessdate=December 26, 2017}}</ref><ref name=mitcci>{{cite web|url=http://cci.mit.edu/people_advisoryboard.html|title=People: Advisory board|website=MIT Center for Collective Intelligence|accessdate=August 8, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150721235929/http://cci.mit.edu/people_advisoryboard.html|archive-date=July 21, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n<ref name=forbes25>{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/2007/01/23/internet-fame-celebrity-tech-media-cx_de_06webceleb_0123intro.html|title=The Web Celeb 25|first=David M.|last=Ewalt|date=January 23, 2007|accessdate=October 31, 2008|work=Forbes}}</ref><ref name=NewMuseum>{{cite web|title=Stuart Regen Visionaries Series: Jimmy Wales|url=http://www.newmuseum.org/events/438|publisher=New Museum|accessdate=April 6, 2011|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101222115648/http://newmuseum.org/events/438|archivedate=December 22, 2010|url-status=dead}}\n*{{cite web|title=Wikipedia founder 